From: SlayZone Dev <dev@slayzone.local>
Date: Thu, 11 Jun 2026 14:02:51 +0200
Subject: feat(slayzone): hide the Web Store "Switch to Chrome?" nag in the
 inlay
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

That nag is served only to non-Chrome browsers via Google's proprietary
X-Client-Data signal — which a Chromium fork can't legitimately satisfy, so the
UA brand alone can't suppress it (and faking X-Client-Data is a bad idea, it
steers Google's field-trial config). Instead, a NagHider WebContentsObserver on
the extensions inlay's Web Store tab injects, at navigation COMMIT
(document-start, so no flash), an isolated-world script that hides the promo by
TEXT match ("recommends using chrome" / "switch to chrome"), piercing shadow
roots and re-hiding via a throttled MutationObserver. Selector-free → durable;
needs refreshing only if Google changes the wording.
